<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="128" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,464,738]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cornejo &amp; Lombardi. A, Cerro Azul" authorityYear="2021" box="[136,286,464,485]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Salacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Celastrales" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="juradoi">
<emphasis box="[136,286,464,485]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Salacia juradoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a new species from coastal 
<collectingCountry box="[585,665,464,486]" name="Ecuador" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
that resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Miers.) A. C. Sm." authorityName="A. C. Smith" authorityYear="1939" baseAuthorityName="Miers." baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[818,1159,464,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Salacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Celastrales" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="impressifolia">
<emphasis box="[818,967,464,485]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">S. impressifolia</emphasis>
(Miers.) A. C. Sm.
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by the opposite to decussate arrangement of leaves, larger leaf blades, narrowly oblong to oblong, sometimes narrowly-lanceolate, 
<quantity box="[1279,1375,500,521]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" unit="cm" value="22.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="14.0">14–30 cm</quantity>
(versus elliptic, rarely ovate, obovate or lanceolate, [3.4–] 
<quantity box="[668,787,535,557]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.21" metricValueMax="1.42" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" unit="cm" value="12.1" valueMax="14.2" valueMin="10.0">10–14.2 cm</quantity>
), margin with scattered dark-brown marginal glands (vs. eglandular), flower buds oblate, light-green, white-pulverulent (versus globose, ferrugineous), margin of sepals often ciliate or ciliolate (vs. glabrate), petals patent, erose (vs. deflexed, entire), outer margin of disk entire (vs. fimbriate), and fruit with pericarp smooth (vs. verrucose).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
